Thank you for trying ArcOS.  To try out ArcOS, please read the following instructions.

1. Requirements
To build ArcOS binary, you need:

cmake version 2.4 or after
gcc version 3.4
g++ version 3.4

Please make sure these programs are ready in your host computer.

2. Build

- Make a build directory, for example:
  % cd $ARCOS_SOUCE_DIR
  % mkdir build

- Run cmake in the build directory.
  % cd build
  % CC=gcc-3.4 CXX=g++-3.4 cmake ..

or, run ccmake to further configurations.
  % cd build
  % CC=gcc-3.4 CXX=g++-3.4 ccmake ..

- Run make and install.
  % make
  % make install

